When you define a LinkedHashMap as `LinkedHashMap<String, String> sections;`, you're telling Java that the keys and values of the map are both Strings. However, when you try to compare a string with a value from the map, you're actually comparing an Object with a String. This is because the values in a map are Objects, not Strings.

To compare a string with a value from the map, you need to convert the Object to a String. You can do this using the `toString()` method, like this:

```java
String nextSection = me.getValue().toString();
if (line.contains(nextSection)) {
    System.out.println("Line contains next section");
